<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>open a book on something • open book, an</xh5><p> <i>open a book on something</i>—(Bookmakers) take bets on certain contests: There is a good deal of interest in the outcome of this ballot, so I thought it might be fun to <u>open a book on</u> the event.</p><p> <i>open book, an—</i>used of a person or thing that can be readily examined or understood: He kept to himself personally, but his military life was <u>an open book</u>.</p><p> <i>See also: close the book on something / close the books on something.</i></p> </entry>
